MAINTENANCE & OPERATION TIPS

Recommended Maintenance every 90-120 days:

Turn Power OFF. Disconnect power supply

and wave pump from HUB. Remove pump
from aquarium.

Carefully remove pump from swivel bracket

Fill a container with a 1:1 ratio of distilled
and disassemble into components.

vinegar and fresh water. Soak pump in
solution 4-12 hrs.

Rinse components under fresh water and Carefully re-assemble pump, rinse in fresh
gently scrub any algae or dirt away using water. Replace prefilter guard with new
a small brush. Soak in solution overnight. foam guard (if being used).

Re-install wave pump back into posltion,
re-connect to HUB. Connect 24V DC power
and adjust direction, flow as desired.

NOTE: Placing hand directly in front of
pump can unbalance impeller and push
water out sides (appear to be running backwards)

To re-balance impeller:

1. Turn power off. Disconnect pump from HUB.

2. Remove pump from water.

3. Remove pump

4. Place pump back in original location, connect to HUB
and reconnect power. Pump will now operate normally.
